[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man charged with Rotherham child sex offences

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has been charged with 45 offences relating to child sexual exploitation in Rotherham, according to South Yorkshire Police.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Arshid Hussain, 40, of High Street, East Cowick, East Yorkshire has been charged with indecent assault and unlawful sexual intercourse.
He has also been charged with unlawful imprisonment and assault.
Mr Hussain has been bailed to appear before Rotherham Magistrates' Court on 25 June.
He is additionally charged with causing a child to be removed from their parent and procuring of a female to have sexual intercourse.
The force said he had been charged as part of Operation Clover, a joint investigation by South Yorkshire Police in partnership with Rotherham Metropolitan Borough Council and the Crown Prosecution Service.
